   Get Involved!
   Related links: INEEL Reporter


                              INEEL Public involvement number, 1-800-708-2680
               Information about the INEEL's CERCLA disposal facility design.


   Comment on the proposed plan for Waste Area Group 10.

   INEEL encourages public involvement and citizens are encouraged to get
   involved in decision-making. Dialogue with citizens improves the
   INEEL's understanding of the public's concerns. We are happy to provide
   the following information and resources:
     * Share your comments.
       We are soliciting comments on the proposed plan for remediation of
       contaminated land surface areas across the INEEL including the
       Eastern Snake River Plain Aquifer (referred to as Waste Area Group
       10). You can send us your comments online, or by calling the
       Community Relations Office at (800) 708-2680. Also, public meetings
       are scheduled for February 7, 2002 at the Double Tree Inn downtown
       in Boise, and for February 12, 2002 at the Shilo Inn in Idaho
       Falls. INEEL staff will be available at 6:00 p.m. to answer
       questions with the formal meeting starting at 7:00 p.m. The comment
       period ends February 27, 2002.
     * Call the INEEL toll-free number, 1-800-708-2680 to request specific
       documents; request a speaker or briefing on a particular topic;
       inquire about public meetings or public comment periods; schedule a
       tour of INEEL; provide oral comments; or request other information.
     * Take a tour. Contact the INEEL Community Relations Office; (800)
       708-2680
     * Find information and review documents. Public Documents Web site
     * Attend public meetings and briefings. Check out the Events Calendar
       and INEEL's Seminar Series, or informal briefings can be scheduled
       for interest groups, civic organizations and local and tribal
       governments. Call the INEEL Community Relations Office, (800)
       708-2680.
     * Learn more. Scheduling an informal briefing or taking a tour are
       some of the ways 31,385 people learned more about the INEEL in
       2000. Last year, INEEL representatives gave 297 presentations to
       schools, colleges, youth groups, civic organizations, technical and
       trade businesses, educator forums and community events.
       During the summer, 7,099 people - 1,009 from 22 foreign countries -
       toured the Experimental Breeder Reactor-I, a National Historic
       Landmark. An additional 2,395 people participated in 176 tours at
       the INEEL.
       For more information about scheduling a tour or a briefing, call
       the INEEL at (800) 708-2680.
       Your personal radiation dose interactive exercise (Requires the
       Macromedia Shockwave plug-in.)
       About Plutonium Fact Sheet
       About Spent Nuclear Fuel
       Radiation Fact Sheet
       Groundwater Fact Sheet
     * Contact independent advisory/oversight/citizen groups
          + Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board
          + Environmental Surveillance, Education and Research
            Contact: ajensen@stoller.com
          + EPA Region 10
          + INEEL Citizens Advisory Board - The INEEL Citizen's Advisory
            Board is a federally chartered organization of independent
            citizens, dedicated to providing informed recommendations on
            issues specific to the INEEL and of impact to the DOE Idaho
            Operations Office, EPA Region 10, and the state of Idaho.
            In 2000, the 15-member board reviewed numerous issues related
            to the INEEL, including:
               o Incineration at the Waste Experimental Reduction Facility
               o Plans for evaluating ecological health at the site
               o Rehabilitation of areas affected by wildfire, and
               o Proposed cleanup plans.
            Meetings are open to the public.
          + Idaho Department of Environmental Quality
          + Idaho Oversight Program
          + Nuclear Regulatory Commission
          + State and Tribal Government Working Group

